name: Jacob Wolf
tweet: I share this for a few reasons:  First, I'm very proud of the work we've done the past four years.  Two, if you believe in yourself, work hard and remain patient, good things will come.  And lastly, don't let age deter you. It's not 'just a number' but it is what you make of it.

name: Jacob Wolf
tweet: But fate ran its course and @darink a few weeks later sent me a job application and later that week, @pbecquey called and asked me to fly to Bristol a few days later.  My first interview there? @Dan_Athletic. My last? @chadmillman. Couple weeks later, job is mine.

name: Jacob Wolf
tweet: I interviewed @chadmillman over the phone in my Austin apartment, and needless to say, I was disappointed. I felt, even with the lack of experience, I was the hardest working journalist in esports at the time. I continued my work at Dot, got more reps on camera and busted my ass.

name: Jacob Wolf
tweet: Several months later, I broke news at Dot that @darink was taking the leadership job to oversee the launch. And then a month later, a person from @ESPNPR contacted me to write a story about their three hires. I wasn't one of them.

name: Jacob Wolf
tweet: When I first went after this job, at 18, I cold emailed @Dan_Athletic and we spoke via Skype shortly thereafter. I had worked less than a year as a journalist but was quickly ascending and growing at a rapid pace while at @DotEsports.  I didn't hear back after our initial chat.

name: Jacob Wolf
tweet: We've won two @esportsawards as a group, several Tempest Awards and I took home the Esports Award for Journalist of the Year in 2018. We've expanded from three people at the beginning to now 13 and many other allies within our walls.  Thank you all for supporting us.

name: Jacob Wolf
tweet: Crazy that @ESPN_Esports turns 4 years old next week, starting our fifth year of coverage. Been a wild ride.  We've collaborated with ESPN The Magazine, E:60, SportsCenter, Outside the Lines, ESPN Audio and others and garnered praise and recognition internally and externally.
